<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5145] FileInstall writes .config files back with backslashes escaping spaces in config values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5145</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Fileinstall 3.5.0 added handling of .config file with an expanded syntax for configuration files allowing proper handling of arrays, etc. A great feature.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is one thing that appears to be handled improperly though - if the values in the key/value pairs have spaces in them, the files are written back with backslash escapes for the spaces. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What is the justification for that?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The effect is that the file is different from the original - which is quite a pain for automated installation with files generated from templates. The fake changes become a maintenance nightmare.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It appears that escaping of spaces can be harmlessly removed, and perhaps should not be a part of the feature... &lt;/p&gt;</description>
